cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper presents a new approach to implementing MCMC for probabilistic programming languages using source-to-source transformation and caching. This topic is closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as probabilistic programming is a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed approach, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of continuation passing style and caching suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
